---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — A Day In">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-24 pb-20 sm:px-8">
    <p class="font-display text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-sand-500">About us</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-sea-800">One tested day, off the map.</h1>
    <div class="prose-sea mt-6">
      <p>
        <strong>A Day In</strong> is built on a simple idea: the best places usually aren't the ones
        topping every list. They're a few hours further on, a little harder to reach — and far more
        worth it. So we go, we spend a single day, and we map exactly how we'd do it again.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every itinerary here is hand-tested: a real route, in real order, with the timings, the
        detours, and the insider tips that only come from actually being there. No affiliate-stuffed
        listicles, no “50 things you must do.” Just a day you could follow tomorrow.
      </p>
      <h2>The ocean thread</h2>
      <p>
        Most of the places we love end up near water — so we lean into it. Teal, sand, and salt air
        run through everything we make, on the page and off it.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is a work in progress (and a bit of a playground), powered by
        <a href="https://www.sanity.io">Sanity</a> and <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
